Asia
----
[4] Pakistan (FATA): fatal
Date: Wed 11 Nov 2015
Source: The Express Tribune [edited]
http://tribune.com.pk/story/988973/mohmand-two-minors-reportedly-die-of-measles/


At least 2 minors reportedly died of measles in Ambar tehsil of Mohmand Agency [Federally Administered Tribal Areas, FATA] on [Tue 10 Nov 2015]. An official privy to the development told The Express Tribune the deceased have been identified as the children of a resident of the area. "The children were of aged 2 and 4, respectively," he added.

According to the official, there is a dearth of suitable health facilities in Mohmand Agency to tackle such medical emergencies. "More often than not, patients are treated by unqualified doctors," he said. [Even with adequate medical care, measles may result in death in approximately 1 per 1000 cases. Vitamin A deficiency has been linked to increased morbidity and mortality. - Mod.LM]

However, health officials in Mohmand Agency have not confirmed the deaths. Many of them have also denied there is a measles outbreak in the agency. "We have reason to believe the minors contracted a cold which eventually led to their death," a health official said.

