******
[5] Malaysia
Date: Fri 6 Nov 2015
Source: Malaysian Digest [edited]
http://www.malaysiandigest.com/frontpage/29-4-tile/577881-latest-measles-outbreak-in-malaysia-here-s-what-you-should-know-to-protect-yourself.html


Measles cases are on the rise, affecting caring institutions, schools, and detention centres nation-wide, says Health director-general Datuk Noor Hisham Abdullah, who also cited that 2 children died due to measles this year [2015] compared with one the previous year made on a statement on Thursday night [5 Nov 2015].

Trebling in numbers, there has been up to 37 cases of outbreaks recorded thus far compared with only 11 outbreaks in 2014, Bernama [Malaysian National News Agency] reports.

Case-wise, 602 have been reported (26.3 per million population) compared with 235 cases (7.8 per million population) in 2014 and 195 (6.6 per million population) in 2013.

[Byline: Mushamir Mustafa]

